  "texts": [
    "The change of students' AI interaction profiles from 1st session to 2nd session and from 2nd session to 3rd session are given in Tables 3 and 4, respectively.",
    "Regarding the profile transitions from Session 1 to Session 2, there's a significant shift away from the \"AI-reliant code generator\" profile towards the \"AI-reliant code generator & refiner\" profile, suggesting increased student engagement in refining AI-generated code.",
    "Additionally, a decrease in \"AI-independent coders\" coupled with an increase in \"AI-assisted code refiner\" indicates a growing reliance on AI tools for code refinement even among those initially coding independently.",
    "The overall trend indicates a dynamic adoption of AI assistance in coding practices, with students transitioning towards profiles that leverage AI for both generation and refinement of code.",
    "Regarding the transitions from Session 2 to Sessions 3, there is a substantial rise in the \"AI-collaborative coder\" profile, suggesting a growing preference for active collaboration with AI tools during coding tasks."
  ],
